'''Haridra Nadhi''' is the largest temple tank in [[India]], may be in the World. It is in [[Mannargudi]], [[Thiruvarur District]] of [[Tamil Nadu]].  This is the largest temple tank among all of the Hindu temple.  The [[Rajagopalaswamy Temple, Mannargudi]].

[[File:Haridra_Nadhi,_Mannargudi.jpg]]

==Area==
The area of the temple tank is 23 acres{{convert|23|acre|m2}}

==The temple tank==
Haridhra Nadhi is the temple tank of the [[Rajagopalaswamy Temple, Mannargudi|Rajagopalaswamy Temple]] of the famous town of Mannargudi of Thiruvarur district. The Rajagopalaswamy temple is a vaishnavite temple of the deity Rajagopalaswamy(Krishna).  This is the place where sages performed penance for the darshan of Lord.  This theertha is considered as Jamuna River-Yamuna- and is praised as Haridra Nadhi. The float festival is celebrated here on Aani Poornima day in June–July.

