'''John Howard Furby''' (May 23, 1882 – August 16, 1939) was an [[American people|American]] [[Orthodontist]] who graduated from [[Angle School of Orthodontia]]. Dr. Furby was an instructor at the school of Angle where he devoted his time teaching the students.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Noyes|first1=Harold|title=Lay Education in Orthodontics|journal=Angle Orthodontist|url=http://angle.org/doi/pdf/10.1043/0003-3219(1939)009%3C0167%3ALEIO%3E2.0.CO%3B2|accessdate=14 November 2015}}</ref>

==Life==
He was born in [[Onarga, Illinois]] in 1882. He was the 2nd of the five children. He went to [[Northwestern University Dental School]] in 1903 to obtain in [[Dental Degree]]. To fund his college education, he worked at the [[Chicago Rapid Transit Company]]. He received his dental degree in 1906 and started practicing in [[Barrington, Illinois]]. He then applied and got accepted to [[Angle School of Orthodontia]] when it was reopened again in [[Pasadena, California]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Noyes|first1=Harold J.|last2=Lasher|first2=Matthew C.|title=Resolutions on the death of Dr. John Howard Furby adopted by the Edward H. Angle Society of Orthodontia at their biennial meeting|url=http://www.angle.org/doi/abs/10.1043/0003-3219(1939)009%3C0168%3AED%3E2.0.CO%3B2|publisher=The Angle Orthodontist|accessdate=18 August 2016|pages=168–168|doi=10.1043/0003-3219(1939)0092.0.CO;2|date=1 October 1939}}</ref> After graduating from the school, he opened his Orthodontic practice in Hollywood, California.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=AHA|title=John Howard Furby|journal=Angle Orthodontist|date=1940|volume=10}}</ref>

